          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇨🇳 China plans to inject cash into its largest state-owned banks</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">China plans to inject at least $55.13 Bn into its largest state-owned banks, including the Agricultural Bank of China and Bank of Communications, by June 2025. The move aims to strengthen core capital reserves amid sluggish credit demand and rising bad loans. Last October, China pledged to "significantly increase" debt to revive the economy.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">This marks <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-01-03-2025-wn2-4-chinas-first-major-bank-recapitalization?source=website" target="_blank">China’s first major bank recapitalization</a> since the global financial crisis and is part of a broader economic stimulus package. The funding, expected from special treasury bonds, could expand to $138 Bn (1 trillion yuan) as Beijing seeks to stabilize its financial sector.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
