        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Regulatory clarity:</strong> The SEC’s classification of memecoins as collectibles rather than securities provides a clearer legal framework, potentially encouraging more investors to participate.</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Integration with emerging technologies:</strong> Memecoins increasingly incorporate AI and gamification elements, transforming from mere speculative assets into tokens with practical applications.</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Institutional interest:</strong> The potential launch of memecoin ETFs indicates growing institutional recognition, which could lead to increased legitimacy and investment in this market.</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Community-driven projects:</strong> The success of platforms like pump.fun demonstrates the power of community engagement in driving memecoin popularity, though it also raises concerns about market manipulation.</p>

           <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Celebrity and political endorsements:</strong> High-profile figures like Trump launching their memecoin can create initial hype but may also lead to rapid market saturation and subsequent declines in value.</p>

